<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUN 92 / International Company News: Cummins buys Onan stake from
Hawker
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COLUMBUS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CUMMINS ENGINE, the US diesel engines manufacturer, has acquired the
remaining 36 per cent of Onan Corporation from Hawker Siddeley Overseas
Investments of the UK for Dollars 64m, Reuter reports from Columbus.
Onan, based in Fridley, Minn., makes and sells power generation equipment
for consumer and industrial markets. Cummins has been majority owner since
1986.
Cummins is to finance the purchase temporarily with short-term borrowings
under its bank revolving credit agreement.
</TEXT>
