Canadian building materials subsidiary, but not before 1993, by when United
Westburne should be breaking even.
The group made a FFr1.87bn profit from asset sales last year, in line with
its policy of focusing on its main businesses and curbing debts.
Mr Jean-Louis Beffa, chairman of Saint Gobain, the glass and pipe-making
group, yesterday forecast that net profits this year would exceed last
year's FFr2.5bn.
The US economy showed clear signs of recovery and sales in Germany were
holding up well, he told a shareholders' meeting.
