<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
INTERNATIONALE Nederlanden Group (ING), the Dutch banking and insurance
company, said first-quarter net profit rose by 8.8 per cent to Fl 358m
(Dollars 200m), on turnover up 8 per cent at Fl 12.5bn.
The pre-tax profits of the group's insurance activities rose by 8.5 per cent
to Fl 228m, outstripping a 4.5 per cent increase to Fl 255m at NMB Postbank,
