Strong growth in international lending helped ING's total loan portfolio
expand by 3.1 per cent to Fl 130.4bn in the first quarter compared with the
quarter to December 31 1991. Although growth in the important domestic
lending sector was limited to less than 1 per cent, foreign lending rose by
13.1 per cent.
Fortis, the Belgian-Dutch insurance group, reported a 17.8 per cent rise in
first-quarter net profit to Ecu73.3m (Dollars 56.93m) with all main sectors
except car insurance posting higher results.
Operating profit grew more slowly, rising by 10.6 per cent to Ecu72.0m.
Revenues were up 22.9 per cent at Ecu2.3bn.
The rise in net profit was aided by a sharp increase in capital gains to
Ecu28.6m from Ecu17.0m. The company, formed in 1990 through the merger of
Amev, the Dutch insurer, and its Belgian counterpart Groupe AG, said
full-year capital gains may not reach the 1990 and 1991 levels.
