This USM-traded group, which incurred substantial losses on its hotel and
computing activities in 1990, reported pre-tax profits of Pounds 71,000 for
the half-year to March 31, against losses last time of Pounds 118,000 which
took in a Pounds 320,000 interest provision against the Realstream computing
business.
The outcome was struck after an exceptional Pounds 77,000 (Pounds 130,000),
being its half share of losses on the Highcliff Hotel, Bournemouth, which
were partly offset by property sales surplus, and after an 18 per cent
reduction in interest charges.
