<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUN 92 / MFI publishes pathfinder prospectus
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MFI, the furniture retailer which in 1987 was the subject of the largest
management buy-out then seen, yesterday published the pathfinder prospectus
for its planned reflotation.
It also reported results for the year to end-April. These showed trading
profits up 51.6 per cent to Pounds 73.7m and pre-tax profits of Pounds 8.8m
compared with losses of Pounds 24.2m. Sales rose by 3.8 per cent to Pounds
644.4m.
Had the float taken place before the year began, pre-tax profits would have
been Pounds 67.1m and earnings per share 7.5p. The prospectus promised a
progressive dividend policy.
It said 'the first half of 1992 has seen conflicting signs of a recovery in
consumer confidence'. The post-Christmas sales were strong.
In March and April sales rose more slowly, but since then they have been
broadly in line with the previous year.
The float, expected to value the group at about Pounds 750m compared with
the Pounds 718m buy-out, will raise Pounds 564m for the company, before
expenses.
The group will still have Pounds 100m of debt after the float, close to the
pro-forma Pounds 107.2m of shareholders' funds.
Some of the buy-out backers will sell their shares. Asda, the food retailer
from which the buy-out was made, is expected to sell the 25 per cent stake
it has held since then.
MFI has 11.4 per cent of the Pounds 5.15bn UK furniture market, making it
the leader in a fragmented industry. Its factories produce 60 per cent of
what it sells.
Under an incentive arrangement, Mr Derek Hunt, chairman and chief executive,
will receive Pounds 1.3m, six other directors will receive Pounds 1m each,
and one, Mr Trevor Tellett who joined the board in 1989, will get Pounds
215,000.
The directors have signed three-year service contracts, dated July 1.
Mr Hunt's salary will be Pounds 275,000 a year.
The issue will be priced on July 2, with applications closing on July 10,
and dealings starting on July 17. The basis of allocations will be announced
on July 16.
A quarter of the issue will be sold through a public offer, with 10 per cent
sold through financial intermediaries and the rest placed with institutions,
some in continental Europe.
County NatWest is sponsoring the issue and the brokers are Rowe &amp; Pitman and
Smith New Court.
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
MFI YEAR-END RESULTS (Pounds m)
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                    1989    1990    1991    1992    1992*
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Turnover            601.7   594.9   620.7   644.4      -
Trading profit       91.4    50.9    48.6    73.7   73.3
Pre-tax profit       43.4    (1.9)  (22.7)   10.1   67.1
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
*Pro forma. Assumes Pounds 546.5m net proceeds from float available
throughout the year
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
