<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Oriflame back on track with Pounds 8.89m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Oriflame International, the direct sales cosmetics group, yesterday reported
a return to sales and profits growth and said that the acquisition of the
ACO skin care brand in Sweden, along with expansion in eastern Europe made
for an encouraging outlook.
The year to March 31 saw sales rise by 17 per cent to Pounds 64.7m (Pounds
55.2m) and operating profit jump 74 per cent to Pounds 7.6m (Pounds 4.36m).
Financial income declined to Pounds 632,000 (Pounds 3.16m), but despite this
the rise at the pre-tax level was 47 per cent at Pounds 8.89m (Pounds
6.05m). The favourable comparison was due to an exceptional item of Pounds
2m carried last year.
Despite recession in its main markets the company managed to raise sales by
7 per cent in Scandinavia and by 10 per cent in the UK.
The final dividend is maintained at 8p for an unchanged total of 12p on
earnings per share of 15.7p (10.3p). The shares rose 6p to 170p.
