   ALGIERS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ALGERIA has freed 2,000 suspected Moslem activists from detention centres in
the Sahara desert to mark the feast of Eid al-Adha, officials said
yesterday, Reuter reports from Algiers.
About 1,200 people have been freed from the centres since March 21, out of
