cancelled in January and has since been banned by court order.
Meanwhile, Mr Mohammed Boudiaf, head of state, appealed to Algerians to join
his Patriotic Rally - a new movement which excludes Moslem radical groups
and which the authorities hope will undermine their support. Mr Boudiaf
dismissed calls from two leading political parties, the Socialist Forces
Front and National Liberation Front, to replace the government with one of
national unity.
