<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Chief quits at Northumbrian Fine Foods
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS FOSTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Richard Adams has resigned as chief executive of Northumbrian Fine Foods,
the USM-quoted biscuit and snack maker. He has held the post for 22 years
writes Angus Foster.
Mr Kevin O'Keeffe, a non-executive director, will become non-executive
chairman. Mr John Gibson, group finance director, has been appointed acting
chief executive while a new chief executive is sought.
Mr O'Keeffe said Mr Adams had decided Northumbrian's enlarged size called
for a new style of management. 'There was no bust up,' he said.
Northumbrian's shares fell 2p to 43p. The company said pre-tax profits for
the year to March 31, due to be announced in July, are expected to be about
Pounds 700,000, compared to Pounds 264,000 in the previous period.
</TEXT>
