<TEXT>
Sir, As one who is far from disconcerted by the result of the Danish
referendum on Maastricht, I nonetheless find it odd that in the UK those who
are now shouting the loudest for a referendum are those who used to be
staunch defenders of the sovereignty of the House of Commons.
Isn't a referendum a denial of the sovereignty of parliament?
Bryan Cassidy,
